  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"4c659245-8a47-4497-862f-fd5707d01be2\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>See <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661233/Curves\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661233\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Curves</a> for more information on RenderMan curve and its attributes, curves default to tubes in RenderMan. Camera facing/billboard curves are not supported. but ribbons will be rendered if user normals are supplied.</p></div></div><p /><p>To render the curve, we need to add at least a width attribute unless huge curves and hair are what you want. </p><p>You can use the shelf button<strong> AddSpareParameters</strong> with the curve SOP selected to create the RenderMan tabs and the Geometry Tab for setting Curve properties:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Curve Basis:</strong> Selected the type of curve basis (to influence the shape and control)</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"530\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544643849/rfh_curveBasis.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433120082&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=530&amp;height=245\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544643849/rfh_curveBasis.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433120082&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"390\" data-width=\"841\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544643875\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfh_curveBasis.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544643849\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e22b80f2-4bb3-415d-af24-a97db0618b90\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544643849/rfh_curveBasis.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433120082&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=841&amp;height=390 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544643849/rfh_curveBasis.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433120082&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=530&amp;height=245 1x\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Opacity Samples:</strong> The number of samples to take when using Presence (opacity) in a material. Note that the integrator may be used to enforce a set number of opacity samples before resorting to stochastic samples which may be noisy.</p></li></ul><h2 id=\"Curves-AddWidthAttribute\">Add Width Attribute</h2><ul><li><p>Add a width attribute with <strong>Attribute Create</strong>.  Set a width value at the bottom, e.g. 0.01 and connect the nodes. It will automatically pick up the new value.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"544\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544643849/width_attributecreate.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433119828&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=544&amp;height=299\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544643849/width_attributecreate.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433119828&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"442\" data-width=\"803\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544643866\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"width_attributecreate.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544643849\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"8d4c817e-83a6-4c54-affb-e23ceafe7b3e\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544643849/width_attributecreate.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433119828&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=803&amp;height=442 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544643849/width_attributecreate.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433119828&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=544&amp;height=299 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544643849/rfh_curveWidth.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433120082&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544643849/rfh_curveWidth.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433120082&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"405\" data-width=\"443\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544643878\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfh_curveWidth.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544643849\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e29fdc7d-a732-4e8e-856a-b6a37ad8ba5a\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><p /><p /><p /><h3 id=\"Curves-ROPNodesettings\">ROP Node settings</h3><p>Under <strong>Rendering &gt; Dicing</strong> you will find the global control Minimum Width to control the minimum width in pixels of rendered curves. Smaller values (or 0) may take longer to render as curves smaller than a pixel width may be missed and require more min samples from the rendering quality settings.</p><p />"
    }
